<subSubSection id="1C8A6552A503892E8F6A48F88B5532DA" pageId="29" pageNumber="302" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="542F36D9A503892E8F6A48F88C26321A" blockId="29.[794,1399,457,961]" pageId="29" pageNumber="302">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA503892E8F6A48F88B8D30FA" bold="true" box="[794,897,457,481]" pageId="29" pageNumber="302">Remarks:</emphasis>
<typeStatus id="8B2B887BA503892E8FF948F88BE030FA" box="[905,1004,457,481]" pageId="29" pageNumber="302">Holotype</typeStatus>
of this species is a male from outermost eastern 
<collectingCountry id="2C877649A503892E8FDC48D88BFB331A" box="[940,1015,489,513]" name="Turkey" pageId="29" pageNumber="302">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="9654F83BA503892E887648D88C33331A" box="[1030,1087,489,513]" country="Turkey" name="Igdir" pageId="29" pageNumber="302">Iğdır</collectingRegion>
), but apart from the this, no other Turkish specimens are known. However, 
<bibRefCitation id="30014B28A503892E897A4B388B9E335A" author="WARNCKE, K." pageId="29" pageNumber="302" pagination="145 - 195" refId="ref70981" refString="WARNCKE, K. 1981: Beitrag zur Bienenfauna des Iran 12. Die Gattung Prosopis F., mit Bemerkungen zu weiteren bekannten und unbekannten palaarktischen Arten. - Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Venezia 31 [1980]: 145 - 195." type="journal article" year="1981">WARNCKE (1981: 192)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned 
<specimenCount id="4296FD50A503892E886C4B188CBB335A" box="[1052,1207,553,577]" pageId="29" pageNumber="302" type="generic">146 specimens</specimenCount>
of both sexes as 
<typeStatus id="8B2B887BA503892E8F6A4B7B8B8C3379" box="[794,896,586,610]" pageId="29" pageNumber="302">paratypes</typeStatus>
from 
<collectingCountry id="2C877649A503892E8FB54B7B8BF8337A" box="[965,1012,586,609]" name="Iran" pageId="29" pageNumber="302">Iran</collectingCountry>
. Our knowledge about the range of this species was recently extended by DATHE &amp; PROSH- CHALYKIN (2018) with evidence from five Central Asian countries. While 
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA503892E8FA54B9B8C5B33DA" baseAuthorityName="WARNCKE" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[981,1111,682,705]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="araxanus">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA503892E8FA54B9B8C5B33DA" box="[981,1111,682,705]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="302">H. araxanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widespread and usually has been captured in numbers, it must be classified as rare in 
<collectingCountry id="2C877649A503892E8F164BD88BBD321A" box="[870,945,745,769]" name="Turkey" pageId="29" pageNumber="302">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="CCAB2A5CA503892E8FCE4BD88C13321A" box="[958,1055,745,769]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="68.[211,244,1429,1451]" captionTargetBox="[211,1414,859,1420]" captionTargetId="figure-259@68.[211,1414,859,1420]" captionTargetPageId="68" captionText="Fig. 17: Distribution map of rarely recorded Hylaeus species in Turkey: species collected in only one (1-12) or two (II-X)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5742935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5742935/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="302">Fig. 17.2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="542F36D9A503892E8F6A4A388B5532DA" blockId="29.[794,1399,457,961]" pageId="29" pageNumber="302">
This is amazing, because the species is small, but easy to recognize. The wrinkly-striped forehead region of the males is reminiscent of 
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA503892E88554A7B8C9A327A" baseAuthorityName="FRIESE" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[1061,1174,842,865]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moricei">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA503892E88554A7B8C9A327A" box="[1061,1174,842,865]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="302">H. moricei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but in 
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA503892E88824A7B8D7A327A" baseAuthorityName="WARNCKE" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[1266,1398,842,865]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="araxanus">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA503892E88824A7B8D7A327A" box="[1266,1398,842,865]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="302">H. araxanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the head is wider than long, the punctation, especially of the mesopleura, coarser, and the sculpture smooth and shiny.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
